            <!-- Stemmatics -->
            <note type="stemmatics">OY cites seven mss., and the text is verified by one historic
                  ms., Manisa 1183 (664H taken from an original in IA’s hand) which he did not see.
                  OY erroneously lists Fatih 5322 as having an authenticating samāʿ, but this refers
                  to the next work in the collection, K. Maqṣid al-asmāʿ. According to OY, the same
                  work, entitled Ummuhāt al-maʿārif has been attributed to Abd al-Karīm al-Jīlī, and
                  the author mentions the Fuṣūṣ in the text. According to Pablo Beneito, Abū Tālib
                  al-Makkī and Ibn Sīd al-Baṭalyawsī are also mentioned in the text.</note>
